originalText.text: Edit was so helpful throughout my filing process. I was very nervous but she helped calm my nerves by answering my questions in detail, got on the phone to understand my situation thoroughly, and gave great advice. I am so grateful for her help and would have been lost without her guidance. Thank you, Edit!

originalText.text: I didn't even see Edit's impeccable reviews online on Google/Avvo before hiring her, and now I have renewed faith in unanimous 5-star ratings. Edit came through a friend's recommendation and her warm advice, willingness to chat even before engaging her formally, and competitive pricing easily sealed the deal and made her stand head and shoulders above other options. She stayed communicative, understanding and efficient throughout a very opaque and unintuitive process. My green card application was fraught with emotion and uncertainty, but Edit gave me sound reasons to feel confident, and we were, in fact, pleasantly surprised with how smoothly everything went. Her fees are easily the BEST money I've spent in my life. I would highly recommend her to anyone, without reservation. Someone called her the best immigration lawyer in NYC - but I live in California and got top-tier service and availability from her, and wish she did more than immigration law.

originalText.text:
Words cannot express how grateful and thankful I am for Edit!
I contacted her because my green card was denied. She took over my case and
represented me extremely well and in due time everything was taken care of.All phone calls were taken or returned, all emails were answered. I never felt out of the loop.She was kind, professional, and understanding.
I was able to worry less knowing that my case was entrusted with her.
She won my case, and due to her excellent knowledge of immigration law I became a permanent resident of the U.S.
She is THE BEST immigration lawyer in NYC!!!!
I highly recommend her services!!!!

Thank you, Edit!

originalText.text: Edit is the best, she helped me out during an extremely stressful time in my immigration process. I had a VERY tight deadline and she was always very quick to respond and answered all of my questions. Not only that, I always felt that I could trust her and that she had my best interests at heart. Very important to trust your lawyer for something as paramount as your immigration status! She made an unbearable situation more bearable, cannot recommend her enough :)
